	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm sorry to see your guild is so Uber they can play favorites.&nbsp;&nbsp;But please do not assume that all guilds must use NBG for sweet stuff like this.  They don't.  My guild would never assign this piece to anyone on a 'need' basis because there is a real strong argument for any class to equip this item.<br><br>Plain and simple, all killed, all can equip, all who wish to roll on the item have earned the right to do so if it is their belief that the piece will significantly improve their stats.  Whether or not my characters would roll on the item would depend entirely on which character was on scene and what equipment was worn by the other guild members on the team scoring the item.  In all likelihood all of my characters would roll on this because it does such great things for them all.<br><br>As far as a Guild 'has' to assign loots, hogwash and puppy spackling!  A guild made of friends, not of greedy loot hogs, will invariably see the gear that drops landing on the right player/class combination.  And such a guild will succeed in ways that the so called uber guilds never will.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
